org.waarp.openr66.client
Class SpooledDirectoryTransfer

java.lang.Object
  org.waarp.openr66.client.SpooledDirectoryTransfer
All Implemented Interfaces:
Runnable
public class SpooledDirectoryTransfer
extends Object
implements Runnable

Direct Transfer from a client with or without database connection or Submit Transfer from a client with database connection to transfer files from a spooled directory to possibly multiple hosts at once.
Hosts will have to be separated by ','.

Mandatory additional elements:
-directory source (directory to spooled on)
-statusfile file (file to use as permanent status (if process is killed or aborts))
-stopfile file (file when created will stop the dameon)
Other options:
-regex regex (regular expression to filter file names from directory source)
-elapse elapse (elapse time between 2 checks of the directory)
-submit (to submit only: default)
-direct (to directly transfer only)

Author:
Frederic Bregier
